{
  "stem": "19210.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 236.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because at the time, I spoke Portuguese, a little bit Latino, a few words here and there of French, and in fact, a few words of [?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Magarbe, ?] which was the dialect spoke by the-- by the Moroccan Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But one day, or I should say perhaps one noon, I was there working, helping with the setup of the tables, and I noticed that a family walked in very well-dressed, not like the refugees which were dressed in drab clothing and so forth.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But what really prompted me to raise a question was they were speaking fluent Portuguese.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I approached the man and I said, excuse me, sir, in Portuguese, this dining room is for the refugees.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The Portuguese dining room is on the other side.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So the man kind of laughed a little and he said, we, too, are refugees.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And-- and that was a little bit puzzling to me because I was a young man, teenager, I-- I knew there was a war going on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You heard-- you read the papers, you heard comments at the synagogue, et cetera and I was surprised when he said that we, too, are refugees.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I ask him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was very questionable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, how is is it that you are refugees?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You are Portuguese.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he says, sit down, young man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Sit down.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I sit down and this man began to tell me a story.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He told me, I'll tell you why I am a refugee.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he said, my name is Dr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Aristides de Sousa Mendes, [PORTUGUESE].",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
